HEADWORD: Tropism
<hw>Tro"pism</hw> <pr>(tr⟦omac⟧"p⟦icr⟧z'm)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>troph`</grk> a turning, <grk>tre`pein</grk> to turn +
<ets>-ism</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Modification of the
direction of growth, caused by some external influence, such as light;
-- sometimes used for motion of an organism toward or away from an
external stimulus, more properly called <contr>taxis</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tropist</ent>⟦br⟧
